n the form of the mixed ODE-PDE system. The obtained\nresults are illustrated by example of the sex ratio model which shows that when\ndifferent mortalities of both sexes are assumed, the sex ratio of 0.5 is\nobtained but that Fisher's mechanism driven by the reproductive value of the\ndifferent sexes is not in equilibrium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Mar 2013 19:23:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2020 21:02:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 31 Aug 2020 16:46:46 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 31 Mar 2021 16:17:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-01"}
