itical temperature can be equal to 764 K, which very\nwell correlates with Tc for metallic hydrogen (p=2 TPa). Other parameters\n($R_{\\Delta}$, Rc, and $R_{H}$) should not deviate from the predictions of the\nBCS theory more than the analogous parameters for CaH6.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Mar 2013 10:35:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-17"}
